videoSnippet.title: Naka is King || Xiong vs Nakamura || U.S. Championship (2019)
videoSnippet.description:
WATCH GRENKE TRAILER HERE https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=27ec5obgwqg

Follow me on Instagram for extra content https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Jeffery Xiong vs Hikaru Nakamura
US Championship (2019), St Louis, MO USA, rd 11, Mar-31 
Dutch Defense: Leningrad. Matulovic Variation (A89)

1. d4 f5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 g6 4. g3 Bg7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. d5 Na5 9. b3 c5 10. Bb2 a6 11. Ng5 Rb8 12. Qd3 Qe8 13. Nd1 b5 14. Qd2 Nb7 15. Ne3 Nd8 16. Nh3 Bd7 17. Rad1 b4 18. Qc2 a5 19. Nf4 a4 20. h4 Ra8 21. Qb1 Ra6 22. Bf3 Qf7 23. Neg2 Ng4 24. Bg4 fg4 25. e4 Bb2 26. Qb2 Qg7 27. Qg7 Kg7 28. e5 Bf5 29. ed6 ed6 30. Rfe1 Nf7 31. Re7 Kf6 32. Rb7 ab3 33. ab3 Rfa8 34. Ne3 Ra1 35. Kf1 Ne5 36. Ra1 Ra1 37. Ke2 Nf3 38. Nf5 Kf5 39. Ke3 Re1 40. Kd3 Ne5 41. Kd2 Ra1 42. Ne6 h6 43. Rb6 Ra3 44. Kc2 Ra2 45. Kd1 Nd3 46. Rd6 Nf2 47. Ke1 Nd3 48. Kd1 Ke4 49. Nc7 Nf2 50. Ke1 Kd3 51. Rg6 Ne4 52. Kf1 Ng3 53. Kg1 Ne2 54. Kh1 Ke3 55. Rf6 Ra1 56. Kg2 Rg1 57. Kh2 g3 58. Kh3 Rh1

The 2019 U.S. Championship is a 12-player round-robin featuring the strongest players in the USA, who compete for $194,000 in prize money as well as the coveted title of U.S. Champion. If two or more players tie for first place a playoff will be held.

For the 11th consecutive year the Saint Louis Chess Club is hosting the event. Players receive 90 minutes for the first 40 moves followed by 30 minutes for the rest of the game, with a 30-second increment from move one. Draw offers are not allowed before move 30. Official website: uschesschamps.com
